          <div class="bg-blue-500 text-white p-4 relative rounded-out-lg font-mono">rounded-out-lg</div>
          <div class="bg-blue-500 text-white p-4 relative rounded-out-xl font-mono">rounded-out-xl</div>
          <div class="bg-blue-500 text-white p-4 relative rounded-out-2xl font-mono">rounded-out-2xl</div>
          <div class="bg-blue-500 text-white p-4 relative rounded-out-3xl font-mono">rounded-out-3xl</div>
        </div>

        <p class="mt-4">
          Notice that only the bottom corners are rounded out? This is because there's only two psuedo elements
          available to create the corners. And we assume that the default use-case is to round out the bottom corners.
        </p>

        <hr />
         
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold">Nesting</h3>
        <p>If you want to round out <strong>all sides</strong>, you can nest the element
          <code class="bg-slate-200 rounded px-1 py-1 text-fuchsia-600">rounded-out-lg</code> inside another <code
            class="bg-slate-200 rounded px-1 py-1 text-fuchsia-600">rounded-out-lg</code
